  "presentation_notes": {
    "opening": "So how does this actually work? It's three simple steps.",
    "step_by_step": {
      "step_1": "[Point to left card] Step one: Deploy at the source. You install Expanso agents where your data lives—edge devices, Kubernetes clusters, cloud VPCs, on-prem data centers. [Pause] And here's the key: No application changes required. Your apps keep working exactly as they do today.",
      "step_2": "[Point to middle card] Step two: Define your rules. You set policies using simple, declarative rules. 'Drop debug logs.' 'Mask PII fields.' 'Send errors to Splunk.' 'Keep 10% of metrics.' It's all git-based configuration—Infrastructure as Code. Your data team already knows how to do this.",
      "step_3": "[Point to right card] Step three: Watch costs drop. Data flows optimized to your platforms. 50 to 70 percent less data ingested. Immediate cost reduction. Faster queries. Better compliance. [Pause] And you see results within 24 hours of deployment."
    },
    "timeline": "[Point to bottom] Total time to value? Two to four weeks from contract to production. Not months. Not quarters. Weeks.",
    "transition": "Now let me show you what this looks like in a real customer example...",
    "pacing": "Move deliberately through each step. Don't rush. Each card deserves attention."
